“We have gone to the county commander of police, Maua and Meru police but no response is forthcoming. The government should tell us where they are since the DCI officers who went there and said they were government officers should have identified them through their service numbers,” said Mr Mugambi. 

Ms Makena said the twist in the disappearance saga had caused anxiety in the family. 

Police in Meru have also released a Toyota Probox in which the three were traveling on the day they went missing. 

